    "title": "Jack Daniel's Series of Releases",
    "body": "Jack Daniel’s has produced a variety of special series releases over the years, each with its unique characteristics and appeal. We are currently working out building documentation around all these releases! Below is a list of some notable series with links to our posts about them: Holiday Select: Released annually during the holiday season, featuring unique batches.  2011 2012 2013 2014Tennessee Tasters’ Selection and Distillery Series: Limited releases hand-selected by Jack Daniel’s tasters and employees.  Tennessee Tasters’ High Angel’s Share Barrels (2018) Tennessee Tasters’ Hickory Smoked (2018) Tennessee Tasters’ Series Barrel Reunion 1 (2019) Tennessee Tasters’ Barrel Proof Rye (2019) Tennessee Tasters’ Series Barrel Reunion 2 (2020) Tennessee Tasters’ Series Jamaican Allspice (2020) Tennessee Tasters’ 14E19 ‘Twin’ Blend Whiskey (2020) Distillery Series Maple Barrel Rye (2022) Distillery Series Toasted Oak Barrel Rye (2022) Distillery Series Pecan Wood (2022) Distillery Series Anejo Tequila Barrels (2022) Distillery Series Oloroso Sherry Casks Distillery Series Twice Barreled Tennessee Straight Rye Whiskey (2024)Master Distiller Series: A tribute to the men who have overseen the distillation process at the Jack Daniel Distillery.  Master Distiller No. 1 - Jack Daniel Master Distiller No. 2 - Jess Motlow Master Distiller No. 3 - Lem Tolley Master Distiller No. 4 - Jess Gamble Master Distiller No. 5 - Frank Bobo Master Distiller No. 6 - Jimmy Bedford Master Distiller No. 7 - Jeff ArnettLegacy Edition: Celebrates the history of Jack Daniel’s with retro labels and unique flavors.  Legacy Edition 1 Legacy Edition 2 Legacy Edition 3Gold Medal Series: Commemorates the gold medals won by Jack Daniel’s whiskey at various international expositions.  1904 St. Louis World’s Fair 1913 Ghent 1914 London 1915 San Francisco 1954 Brussels 1981 AmsterdamSinatra Select: A special edition honoring Frank Sinatra’s love for Jack Daniel’s.  Sinatra Select Sinatra CenturyBottled-in-Bond: Honors the Bottled-in-Bond Act of 1897, ensuring quality and authenticity.  Bottled-in-BondGentleman Jack: Double mellowed for exceptional smoothness.  Gentleman JackThis list captures some of the prominent series and special releases from Jack Daniel’s. Each series and release offers a unique taste and story, reflecting the rich history and craftsmanship of the distillery. "
